1. Bash scripts use the .sh extension while Python scripts use the .py extension.

2. Every bash script in the lab used #!/bin/bash at the beginning.

3. # is the character used to display comments in Python. These are used by the creator to help readers understand the program.

4. Bash scripts are the default in the terminal emulator environment, while Python scripts are not. There are also different versions of Python, which is why Python3 
must be chosen. 
